tweet: (14/14) Final Thoughts:  No more monthly metrics from $VYGVF which could cause more volatility as people (like me) speculate on activity.  Ranking in the App store may be the best metric we have.  If volatility picks up, I may trim. Wish there were options. Maybe an uplisting?

name: Hot Stocks Luke
tweet: (13/14) Final Thoughts:  I will hold Voyager at least into Wednesday as the stock will get some energy into the $COIN debut.  If $COIN holds its open price, I expect to hold the stock until Q1 earnings in May.  https://t.co/xLyPBh2o0m

name: Hot Stocks Luke
tweet: (12/14) Valuation:  ü§∑‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏èü§∑‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏èü§∑My hope was that $COIN would debut at 50x revs and would cause a major rocket for Voyager.  That said, $VYGVF should have AT LEAST DOUBLE the ratio as $COIN because the growth is so much higher.

name: Hot Stocks Luke
tweet: (11/14) Valuation:  $COIN will open with a valuation of AT LEAST $100B.  $COIN $1.8B Q1 rev * 4 qtr = $7.2B rev run rate  $100B / 7.2B = 13.9x EV/S  This is OK for $VYGVF. The multiple isnt as crazy as initial expectations bc $COIN rev was much higher than I est.

name: Hot Stocks Luke
tweet: (10/14) Valuation:  $55M/qtr is $220M/yr of rev assuming NO growth.  $3.45B EV / $220M rev = 15.7x Sales  That is not cheap, but assumes no growth and revenue rose from $3.5M to $55M from Q4 to Q1.  If they only doubled revenue by the end of the year, that valuation is fine.  https://t.co/mGq044d3Lb

name: Hot Stocks Luke
tweet: (9/14) üö®Estimating Q1 Revenue:  We do not expect the qtr results to come out until late May, which isnt ideal because there could be a lot of stock volatility between now and then. So, I wouldn‚Äôt hold just for earnings right now despite my expectation the numbers will be good.

name: Hot Stocks Luke
tweet: (8/14) Estimating Q1 Revenue:  $30.8M in March + $20M in Feb + 8.6M in Jan = $59.4M Q1 revenue.  This is slightly higher than my previous estimate of $55.4M.  Analyst estimate is $46M with the street high (3 analysts) at $53M.

name: Hot Stocks Luke
tweet: (7/14) Estimating Q1 Revenue:  95K new funded accounts in March vs 75K new funded accounts in Feb.  270K total funded accounts * $114/funded account = $30.8M revenue.  Because I would expected new funded accounts to trade more than existing, this revenue estimate could be light.  https://t.co/6dQ1QVyYCv

name: Hot Stocks Luke
tweet: (6/14) Estimating Q1 Revenue:  The company makes about half of its money from trade activity and half from lending. We did NOT get trade activity for the first time, so instead we will rely on funded accounts.  Feb Revenue $20M / 175K funded accounts = $114/funded account.  https://t.co/2Jun9ShDlF

name: Hot Stocks Luke
tweet: (5/14) Coinbase $COIN IPO Thoughts:  The stock has moved 15%/day on no news (and 4,000% over 6 mo) so news could cause high volatility.  A med-term benefit is that once $COIN and eToro ($FTCV) start trading, $VYGVF could get more analyst coverage from banks covering the sector.

name: Hot Stocks Luke
tweet: (4/14) Coinbase $COIN IPO Thoughts:  That said, there is already a lot of excitement coming into the CB debut.  If the $COIN valuation gets too run up before trading starts and $COIN shares trade below the open price, we will have trouble.  $COIN open price is your line to watch

name: Hot Stocks Luke
tweet: (11/10)  Rather than panic selling when I see my account down 10k in the morning, this is the type of thinking I go through:  - Why do i own the stock? - Is valuation fair? - Does my thesis hold up  and sell the stocks which don't support my thesis anymore.

name: Hot Stocks Luke
tweet: (10/10) In conclusion: The volatility sucked. But I own the stock awaiting Coinbase and Robinhood IPOs (it should pop)  The expected Q1 revenue beat & OK valuation increase my conviction to wait out volatility.

name: Hot Stocks Luke
tweet: (9/10) Other items of interest: - Coinbase $COIN IPO - Robinhood IPO - Crypto credit/debit cards - Crypto prices increasing? Would cause major fomo again - Plenty of cash, just raised

name: Hot Stocks Luke
tweet: (8/10) The average PS for the Nasdaq is 4.5x versus 13.6x for $VYGVF  So, you are paying a lot. But, we are taking about a co that increased revenue from 3.5M to 55M in 1 qtr  I am fine paying 13.6 times now, bc if they only 2x rev through 2021, you are inline with a small stock

name: Hot Stocks Luke
tweet: (7/10) Valuation:  $55.6M in Q1 * 4 quarters = $222M of annual revenue assuming NO growth. Revenue was $3.5M in Q4 and we expect it to increase almost 20x Q/Q, so there should be growth.  $3,000M market cap / $220M ann revenue = 13.6x P/S

name: Hot Stocks Luke
tweet: (6/10) $42M analyst estimate for Q1 versus my $55.6M estimate  This is something which helps me put the volatility out of mind and reminds me why I hold this stock

name: Hot Stocks Luke
tweet: (5/10) Is this estimate defendable? I think so:  - It assumes no new accounts in March - #11 in finance apps $VYGVF - The account waitlist is off which we had in Feb - Interest promotions from the company  Crypto being less FOMO this month is the biggest problem  https://t.co/vcQRWgqLJP

name: Hot Stocks Luke
tweet: (4/10) 175K funded accounts entering the month * 15 trades = 2.6M total trades  2.6M trades * $10.20/trade = $26.8M of revenue in March  üö®Q1 Revenue Expectation = $8.6M Jan + $20M Feb + $27M Mar = $55.6M

name: Hot Stocks Luke
tweet: (3/10) Now we need to estimate trades for March  175,000 funded accounts as of Feb 28th, up from 106,000 on Feb 4th. Total trades were around 2.1M.  If we say account growth & total trades were linear in Feb:  140K avg accounts/2,100K trades = 15 trades/funded account

name: Hot Stocks Luke
tweet: (2/10)  Q1 Revenue Estimate:  Interest revenue is material, but I focus on trades as a proxy bc we have more data from Voyager about trade activity.  The company averaged 70K trades/day in Feb w/ $20M of revenue.   This means the company earned an average of $10.20/trade.  https://t.co/E1ypTDRYoz
